> What happens when the user request /dev/dsp1 ?
> A request for sound-slot-1?  I want to load the sb module in this case...
Yes . You don't however have all the control you need because if you access
dsp1 you need to load the driver for dsp0 first or they end up in the
wrong places. Adding "unit=" to the drivers is trivial but it missed the
original 2.2 cut off
